  "prompt": "What's Home Depot's return/exchange policy?",
  "response": "Home Depot's return policy generally allows you to return most new, unopened merchandise within **90 days** of purchase for a full refund. Here's a more detailed breakdown, keeping in mind that policies can sometimes change, so it's always a good idea to double-check with your local store or the Home Depot website:\n\n**Key Highlights:**\n\n*   **90 Days:** Most new, unopened merchandise can be returned within 90 days of purchase.\n*   **Proof of Purchase Required:** A valid receipt, Home Depot card used for the purchase, original order confirmation email, or packing slip is required.\n*   **Refund Method:** Refunds are generally issued in the same form as the original payment.\n*   **Online Purchases:** Online purchases can be returned either in-store or by mail.\n*   **Special Order Returns:** Special order returns have special stipulations and can vary, so confirm with Home Depot directly. They often involve a restocking fee.\n*   **Holiday Returns:** During the holiday season, Home Depot sometimes extends its return policy. Check their website or ask in-store for specific details.\n\n**Items with Specific Return Policies:**\n\n*   **30-Day Returns:**\n    *   **Major Appliances:** Refrigerators, washers, dryers, ranges, dishwashers (unless defective).\n    *   **Gas-Powered Equipment:** Lawn mowers, generators, chainsaws, trimmers.\n*   **No Returns:**\n    *   **Gift Cards:**\n    *   **Labor or installation costs**\n    *   **Custom products:** e.g. custom blinds or paint\n*   **Other Considerations:**\n    *   **Opened Merchandise:** Returns of opened merchandise are generally accepted, but they are subject to the store manager's discretion. It's best to have a valid reason for the return.\n    *   **Defective Items:** Defective items can often be returned or exchanged even outside the standard return window, but it's best to contact Home Depot customer service or a store manager to discuss your options.\n    *   **Paint:** Paint that has been tinted or mixed to your specifications is generally not returnable unless there is a defect in the paint itself.\n    *   **Flooring:** Installed flooring is generally not returnable.\n*   **Haul-Away Fee:** This fee is non-refundable if you're returning an appliance.\n\n**How to Return Items:**\n\n*   **In-Store:** Take the item(s) you want to return, along with your proof of purchase, to the customer service desk at your local Home Depot store.\n*   **By Mail (for Online Purchases):** Follow the instructions on the Home Depot website for returning online orders by mail. You'll usually need to print a return label and package the item securely.\n\n**Important Tips:**\n\n*   **Keep Your Receipt:** Always keep your receipt or other proof of purchase.\n*   **Inspect Items Carefully:** Inspect items for damage or defects before leaving the store or accepting a delivery.\n*   **Ask Questions:** If you have any questions about the return policy, don't hesitate to ask a Home Depot employee.\n\n**Disclaimer:**\nThis information is based on Home Depot's general return policy, but it may be subject to change. Always check the official Home Depot website or contact their customer service department for the most up-to-date and accurate information. Store policies may also vary.\n",
